        <li data-comment-id="comment_blogAndPostId/blog/comment/1560-11948-15086" data-comment-wp-id="15086"  parent-id="" class="comment level0 collapsable" data-badges-advoice="">
            <div class="entity_block">
                <a class="avatar" href="http://blogs.forbes.com/people/tobyiselin/">
                    <img src="http://0.gravatar.com/avatar/a4860a4aba23f2ecf18d5520712f120e?s=40&amp;d=http%3A%2F%2F0.gravatar.com%2Favatar%2Fad516503a11cd5ca435acc9bb6523536%3Fs%3D40&amp;r=G" alt="Toby Iselin" />
                </a>



                <a class="user_name" href="http://blogs.forbes.com/people/tobyiselin/">
                    Toby Iselin
                </a>


   		<span class="timestamp">7 months ago</span>
    	</div>

    	<div class="comment_content">
    		
<p>Bitcoins have a lot of potential. There are many advantages they have over other currencies/stores of wealth. Yes there will be large swings while this new technology gets off the ground, but as long as bitcoin holders don’t panic and sell during some of the larger swings they’ll be fine. The people who decry bitcoin likely were the same people who said the internet would never become widely accepted and useful.</p> 
<p>If anyone doesn’t want their bits or feels they have too many, please feel free to send them my way!</p> 
<p>1DPyMGa3ECi4UMm9Akz4dRFZ9Kc9Y5vqWK</p>

    	</div>



    	<div class="comment_controls" data-called-out-state="off">
			<div class="right_col">
				<a href="http://www.forbes.com/sites/timworstall/2013/12/09/testing-shillers-nobel-prize-against-the-bitcoin-bubble/?commentId=comment_blogAndPostId/blog/comment/1560-11948-15086" class="permalink">Permalink</a>
