        </div>
    </li>



        <li data-comment-id="comment_blogAndPostId/blog/comment/1560-11948-15087" data-comment-wp-id="15087"  parent-id="" class="comment level0 collapsable" data-badges-advoice="">
            <div class="entity_block">
                <a class="avatar" href="http://blogs.forbes.com/people/petershiff/">
                    <img src="https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/-XdUIqdMkCWA/AAAAAAAAAAI/AAAAAAAAAAA/4252rscbv5M/photo.jpg?sz=50" alt="Peter Shiff" />
                </a>



                <a class="user_name" href="http://blogs.forbes.com/people/petershiff/">
                    Peter Shiff
                </a>


   		<span class="timestamp">7 months ago</span>
    	</div>

    	<div class="comment_content">
    		
<p>Given BTC is a new concept, here is a valid argument that states as adoption goes from zero to saturation point BTC will naturally experience a period of exponential growth.</p> 
<p>This growth looks like a bubble because most investors are familiar with the behaviour of more mature markets or post IPO stock prices.</p> 
<p>If BTC fails all the people who cried tulips will believe they were right, if BTC continues to be adopted they will go on crying tulips until the market has matured.</p> 
<p>I personally see the mania in all the other copy coins which seem to serve no purpose other than to speculate on.</p> 
<p>Time will tell.</p>

    	</div>



